\fs22\fsmilli11400 \cf19 \strokec19 IMPORTANT: IDENTIFIER DATA TYPE\
\cf18 \strokec18 To prevent integer overflow and support future growth, all\'a0identifiers\'a0(e.g., booking IDs, RoomTypeID, and other key fields)\'a0must be stored and processed using a 64-bit integer type\'a0(such as\'a0
\f5\fs27\fsmilli13680 \cf7 \cb16 \strokec7 BIGINT
\f1\fs22\fsmilli11400 \cf18 \cb1 \strokec18 ,\'a0
\f5\fs27\fsmilli13680 \cf7 \cb16 \strokec7 Long
\f1\fs22\fsmilli11400 \cf18 \cb1 \strokec18 , or the equivalent in your technology stack).\

\fs20\fsmilli10200 Do not use 32-bit integers (
\f5\fs24\fsmilli12240 \cf7 \cb16 \strokec7 INT
\f1\fs20\fsmilli10200 \cf18 \cb1 \strokec18 ). Once an identifier exceeds the limit, it may overflow and result in incorrect values, data loss, runtime errors, or inconsistent system behavior.\
